result.name: Ashoka Indian Restaurant

reviews.text: I have been customer of this restaurant for more than 5-6 years.  Today having quick lunch and the food was average, not as good when the old shop owner engaged fully of business.  His 2nd generation should pay more effort to improve the food and consider to slightly increase the price.  Food quality is always built on price!
Nice service, nice food 😋

I am a fan of indian food, especially curries, and it's really amazing that I am able to find this traiditional Indian Restaurant in the old residential area of Hong Kong Island. 

The restaurant really offers a no-frills and budget option for neighbours in Shau Kei Wan. The various lunch sets cost less than HK$50, and it even offers discount for students, so they are really lucky to be readily affordable to this tasty cuisine. 

There are various different menu of curries and other Indian dishes serve here. My favorites is of course chicken curries. The chicken was tender and yummy. I also like their fish and prawn dishes, which are very dilicious! The curry is not spicy, and it reminds me of my familiar flavours of traditional Indian cuisine. I am so delighted that It serves with unlimited rice and naah, which sufficient enough to satisfy my large appetite!

Like most people, I started switching to a more healthy eating habit, and it's great that the restaurant also offers a reasonable selection of menus dedicated to vegetarian. My favourite is tomato vegetable and potato curries. 

The small place creates a friendly environment and a casual dining atmosphere, which offers only a limited number of seats. So it's not strange that the place is always packed. So I sometimes prefer take-away my lunch set, which only cost HK$40.  The portions were very generous and definitely worth the price!
Very price to value set lunch and taste of curry and nam is very good despite the restaurant is small
For the price and quality you can't fault the food or the price. A really nice family run establishment.
